Carnage/Teltoli

* Carnage looked around at the darkening sky and saw that the first stars 
were coming out and showing themselves.
She sighed as she laied her head on her clawed hands, it had been a good but 
long day.
Teltoli and her had run most of the way then stopped when they had reached 
the sea borders, it hadn't taken long to catch a fish dinner and settle down 
for the night.
Both bots lay on their sides, absolutely stuffed!
A fire burned between them an crackled in the night, it's red and orange 
light casting shadows along the ground.
Teltoli looked through the fire at Carnage, she levered herself up and 
leaned on one elbow while still in her Beast Mode.*

Teltoli: " Carnage?"

*Carnage looked back at Teltoli through the fire.*

Carnage: " Yeah?"

*The Fuzor sighed and laied her head on her paws, she twitched her nose as a 
stray ash fell upon it.*

Teltoli: " Do you think that we'll ever find the Maximal base? We've been 
searching for days and haven't found a single sign of them."

*Carnage lifted her head from her hands, stretched her neck then laied it on 
the cold ground. She sighed and shrugged.*

Carnage: " To say the truth, I have no clue. We HAVE been looking for days 
and only come across Firestorm, no Maximals."
                                                              *Carnage 
rolled onto her stomach and stretched her legs up towards the sky, she 
wriggled her claws in the air.*

Carnage: "But you never know, we could run into a whole lot of them 
tomorrow, right?"

*Teltoli nodded and relaxed, it was going to be a long night.*
